Abstract
This dissertation presents the design and implementation of an IoT-based smart home system aimed at improving energy efficiency, user convenience and real-time monitoring of household appliances. The motivation for this project arises from the increasing issue of unnecessary domestic energy consumption caused by inefficient appliance usage and lack of user awareness. The project explores how a low-cost, accessible smart home solution can support better energy management through remote control and data-driven insights.
The system was developed using a microcontroller-based platform integrated with sensors and actuators, including a PIR motion sensor, relay-controlled appliances (light and fan) and a servo motor for door control. A mobile application interface was implemented using Blynk, enabling users to remotely control appliances and monitor system activity in real time. The system also includes an energy monitoring feature that estimates energy consumption in watt-hours based on appliance usage and predefined power ratings. In addition, an energy-saving percentage is calculated to provide users with a clear indication of efficiency, alongside live data visualisation through charts displaying consumption and savings over time.
The results demonstrate that the system successfully enables remote appliance control, accurate motion detection and continuous energy monitoring. The implementation of real-time feedback and visualisation improves user awareness of energy usage and encourages more efficient behaviour. Although the energy calculations are based on estimated values rather than direct measurement, the system effectively illustrates consumption patterns and potential savings.
In conclusion, the project achieves its aim of developing a functional smart home prototype that integrates control, monitoring and energy awareness in a single platform. Future improvements could include integrating machine learning for predictive automation, enhancing accuracy with real-time energy sensors and expanding the system for full-scale home deployment.

  
