4.6 Problems Encountered and Solutions
During the development of the smart home energy management system, several technical and implementation challenges were encountered. These issues related to communication stability, hardware integration, automation accuracy and system reliability. Appropriate troubleshooting and corrective actions were applied to ensure stable system performance and successful implementation.
WiFi Connectivity Instability
 
During development, occasional communication problems occurred between the Arduino IDE, internet connection and external library services. These issues affected library downloads, WiFi communication stability and temporary device connectivity during testing and implementation.
 
Figure 4.X: Arduino IDE Connectivity and Library Download Error During Development
Solution: Figure 4.X illustrates one of the connectivity-related issues encountered during implementation. The Arduino IDE temporarily failed to download the required library index from the Arduino server due to interrupted internet communication. In addition, the Arduino Uno R4 WiFi board occasionally displayed connection instability during development. These issues were resolved through stable WiFi configuration, repeated reconnection procedures, restarting the Arduino IDE and validating USB communication settings.
Incorrect Energy Calculations
Initial energy calculations occasionally produced inconsistent values due to timing inaccuracies and rapid dashboard updates. 
Solution: The calculation formula was revised using appliance runtime tracking and controlled percentage boundaries.

RTC Synchronisation Issues
 
Figure 4.X: RTC Library Installation and DS3231 Integration During Development
The DS3231 RTC module initially displayed incorrect timing values during implementation due to improper time configuration and RTC library integration issues within the Arduino environment. Figure 4.X shows the installation and configuration of the RTClib library required for communication between the Arduino controller and the DS3231 RTC module.
Solution: The issue was resolved by correctly configuring the DS3231 backup battery, synchronising the RTC module with the system clock and implementing RTC calibration procedures within the embedded software. Additional testing was conducted to verify accurate scheduling functionality for automation and notification operations.

Relay Switching Problems
Relay modules occasionally triggered unstable switching behaviour during early integration testing. 
Solution: This problem was minimised through improved wiring connections, stable power supply management and repeated hardware validation procedures.

Notification Spam
Frequent notification triggering sometimes resulted in repeated mobile alerts being sent within short periods.
Solution: Timer-based control conditions and notification delay logic were introduced to prevent unnecessary repeated notifications and improve user experience. (Saguna et al. 2020)
